  <title translate="true">GBOB: General-Head-Boundary Observation Package Pane</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">GBOB: General-Head-Boundary Observation Package Pane</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">GBOB: General-Head-Boundary Observation Package</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Features_Tab" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Features</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab of the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Object_Properties_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Object Properties</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box. &#160;This pane is only visible if the GBOB package is selected. &#160;It can only be selected if one or more of the objects being edited defines a General-Head boundary.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The table on this pane is used to specify the observation groups in which this object is included. &#160;The object is included in an observation if the checkbox for the observation is checked. &#160;</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Factor</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is a formula that determines how much of the flow to or from the boundary condition is should be include in the observation at any particular location. &#160;Usually, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Factor</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is set to 1. &#160;See the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Manage_Flux_Observations" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Manage Flow Observations</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box for a more extensive discussion of </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Factor</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><snippet src="Add_or_remove_flux_observation"/></para>
  </body>
